HEADWORD: Hevea
<hw>Hevea</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A small genus of South American
trees yielding latex. It includes the <stype>rubber tree</stype>,
<spn>Hevea brasiliensis</spn>, originally found in South America, but
now used for production of rubber world-wide.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Hevea</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

